  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "They shall lay hold on bow and spear,.... That is, everyone of them should be furnished with both these pieces of armour, that they might be able to fight near and afar off; they had bows to shoot arrows at a distance, and spears to strike with when near. The Targum renders it bows and shields. \"They are cruel, and have no mercy\"; this is said, to strike terror into the hearts of the hardened Jews: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "their voice roareth like the sea; the waves of it, which is terrible, Luke 21:25, ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "their voice roareth like the sea; the waves of it, which is terrible, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Luke 21:25",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and they ride upon horses; which still made them more formidable, as well as suggests that their march would be quick and speedy, and they would soon be with them: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "set in array as men for war; prepared with all sorts of armour for battle: or, \"as a man\" (a); as one man, denoting their conjunction, ardour, and unanimity; being not only well armed without, but inwardly, resolutely bent, as one man, to engage in battle, and conquer or die; see Judges 20:8, ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "set in array as men for war; prepared with all sorts of armour for battle: or, \"as a man\" (a); as one man, denoting their conjunction, ardour, and unanimity; being not only well armed without, but inwardly, resolutely bent, as one man, to engage in battle, and conquer or die; see ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Judges 20:8",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
